-- U.K. Conservatives Lost Votes in 2012, Independent Says
-- B y   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 2013-01-01T14:39:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-01/u-k-conservatives-lost-votes-in-2012-independent-says.html
The U.K. Conservative Party lost a
fifth of its supporters last year,  The Independent  newspaper
reported, citing its own survey of polls.  According to a weighted average of polls last month,
support for the Conservatives fell 7 percentage points, to 32
percent, from the year ago period, while the  Labour party  gained
3 percentage points to 41 percent, the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nandini Sukumar in London at 
 nsukumar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
